HEADWORD: Jemidar
<hw>Jem"i*dar`</hw> <pr>(j⟦ecr⟧m"⟦icr⟧*d⟦aum⟧r`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Per. & Hind. <ets>jama-d⟦amac⟧r</ets>.]</ety> <def>The chief or
leader of a band or body of persons; esp., in the native army of India,
an officer of a rank corresponding to that of lieutenant in the English
army.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>jemadar</asp>,
<asp>jamadar</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Jemlah goat</ent>⟦br⟧
